  <description type="morphology">Annuals, 30–80 cm. Stems sparsely branched; glabrous or glabrate. Leaves: (stipules bristlelike), petiole 1.5–3.5 cm; leaflets 3, blade elliptic, 2–6 × 0.6–1.5 cm, margins entire, weakly sinuate, or serrulate, apex acute, long-acuminate, or mucronate, surfaces glabrate (margins with sparse, relatively long hairs when young). Racemes 1–4 cm (4–30 cm in fruit); bracts unifoliate, obovate, 4–22 mm. Pedicels (green to purple), 8–20 mm. Flowers: sepals persistent, connate 1/2–2/3 of length, purple to green, lanceolate, 1.7–4 × 1–2 mm, margins denticulate, glabrous; petals purple (rarely white), oblong to ovate, 7–12 × 3–6 mm; stamens purple, 18–24 mm; anthers (green), 2–2.3 mm; gynophore 1–15 mm in fruit; ovary 5–7 mm; style 0.1–0.5 mm. Capsules (erect) not inflated, 23–76 × 3–6(–7) mm, striate, (glabrous). Seeds 12–38, black, globose or horseshoe-shaped, 2.8–4 × 2.5–3 mm, rugose. 2n = 34, 60.</description>
